<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-11229] Infinite recursion if exception happens inside exception handler</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-11229</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Use an onException handler like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;onException(Throwable.class).to(&quot;direct:handle_er&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
from(&quot;direct:handle_er&quot;)..throwException(new RuntimeException());&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the main route throws an exception then this will create an infinite recursion of exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would expect that camel handles the exception inside an onException handler differently. So the onException is not called again.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
